    abstract "Communicating personalized information to patients about the
 risks, benefits and other critical information about dental disease and
 treatment is often difficult for providers. In this research we developed a
 novel informed consent prototype that can accurately translate and
 communicate information to patients in a standardized and effective manner
 based on their diagnosis and prescribed treatment. In future work, we aim to
 integrate SmartConsent into the institutional electronic patient record (EPR)
 and determine its effectiveness in a randomized controlled study.",
